r »Lebensform« und dabei eine eigene Wirklichkeit werden.  afunded by OGeSoMo  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMusicxPerformancexPhilosophy and aesthetics. 0aMusicxPerformancexPsychological aspects. 0aMusical perception. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aKörperlichkeit. 4aMetapher. 4aMusikalische Analyse. 4aMusikalische Praxis. 4aMusikausführung. 4aMusikwissenschaft. 4aPerformativität. 4aWahrnehmung. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aCorporeality.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aMetaphor.  aMusic Performance.  aMusical Analysis.  aMusicology.  aPerformativity.2 aOGeSoMoefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839441992zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839441992zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839441992/original  a978-3-11-071955-0 DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA